More than 350 people are the victim of knife assaults every day in England and Wales, the latest crime figures have revealed.Last night a teenager in Lambeth, London, became the latest victim of the stabbing epidemic, dying in hospital after a frenzied attack.Almost 130,000 attacks involved knives last year - equivalent to one every four minutes - according to the annual British Crime Survey.This figure does not include the tens of thousands of assaults against under-16s.